Great idea to add more Linux commands throughout your portfolio! Here are creative suggestions based on your codebase:

## üìç Where to Add Linux Commands

### **1. Home Page (Home.tsx)**
- **`$ ls -la ~/projects`** - Before the "Recent Projects" section
- **`$ cat ~/bio.txt`** - Before your introduction paragraph
- **`$ pwd`** ‚Üí `/home/divyansh/portfolio` - At the very top

### **2. Projects Page (Projects.tsx)**
- **`$ tree ~/projects --depth 2`** - Before the projects list
- **`$ git log --oneline --graph`** - Shows your project history visually
- **`$ find . -name "*.js" -type f | wc -l`** - Fun stat about lines of code
- **`$ docker ps -a`** - For showing your containerized projects

### **3. About Page (About.tsx)**
- **`$ cat /etc/passwd | grep divyansh`** - Before your bio
- **`$ uname -a`** - Show your "system specs" (education/skills)
- **`$ history | tail -5`** - Show recent achievements/activities
- **`$ df -h ~/skills`** - Visual representation of skill proficiency

### **4. Contact Page (Contact.tsx)**
- Already has `$ whoami` ‚úÖ
- Add **`$ ping -c 4 divyansh.joshi`** - "Checking connection status"
- **`$ ssh divyansh@contact.me`** - Interactive prompt before contact info
- **`$ mail -s "Let's Connect" divyansh8065@gmail.com`** - Before email

### **5. Layout/Header (Layout.tsx)**
- **`$ echo $SHELL`** ‚Üí `/bin/developer` - In the header
- **`$ uptime`** - Show how long you've been coding (fun metric)

