GitHub Copilot: GitHub Copilot

Follow these steps to deploy on Cloudflare Pages and fix the SPA blank-screen (React Router) issue.

1) Ensure your build scripts exist (add if missing)
````json
// ...existing code...
{
  "scripts": {
    ...existing code...
    "build": "vite build",
    "preview": "vite preview --port 8080"
  }
}
// ...existing code...
````
2) Add SPA fallback so Cloudflare serves index.html for client-side routes
````
/* /index.html 200
````
3) Verify vite.base is root (for Cloudflare Pages you should NOT use a GitHub-Pages base)
- Confirm in vite.config.ts: base: '/' (no repo subpath).

4) Local test before pushing
- Install & build:
  - npm install
  - npm run build
- Preview locally:
  - npm run preview
  - or: npx serve dist

5) Cloudflare Pages settings to use in the UI
- Connect your GitHub repo (oldregime/my-own-showcase-00).
- Project name: leave or set as you like.
- Root directory: .
- Install command: npm install
- Build command: npm run build
- Output directory: dist
- (Optional) Environment variables: add any API keys if required.
- Enable automatic builds on pushes to your main branch.

6) Push changes and deploy
- git add .
- git commit -m "Prepare Cloudflare Pages: build script + SPA redirect"
- git push origin main
Cloudflare Pages will start a build automatically.

7) Troubleshooting
- If you still see blank page: open browser DevTools Console and check for 404s (missing assets) or wrong base path.
- If client-side routing returns 404 on direct links, ensure public/_redirects is present and pushed.
- Check Cloudflare build logs for errors (missing dependency, build script failures).

This will make the site build to dist and Cloudflare Pages will serve the SPA correctly.

