    Setup Guide - Complete installation instructions
    Deployment Guide - Production deployment strategies
    Troubleshooting Guide - Issue resolution

More docs live under luganode25/documentation/.
Video Demonstration

    Watch the demo: screenshots-and-videos/Divyansh to Luganodes Video.mp4

Technical Architecture
Monitoring Pipeline

Bitcoin Signet Node ‚Üí Grafana Alloy ‚Üí Loki ‚Üí Grafana
                                            ‚Üì
                                   Dashboards & Alerts

Components

    Bitcoin Core: Signet testnet node with comprehensive logging
    Grafana Alloy: Log collection and forwarding agent
    Loki: Log aggregation and storage system
    Grafana: Visualization, dashboards, and alerting platform

Monitoring Capabilities

    Real-time Bitcoin node metrics and logs
    Blockchain synchronization status
    Network connectivity monitoring
    Error detection and alerting
    Performance metrics tracking
    Automated alert notifications

Alert Rules

The system includes 7 comprehensive alert rules:

    Bitcoin Node Down (Critical) - Detects complete node failure
    Chain Reorganization (Critical) - Monitors blockchain stability
    High Error Rate (Warning) - Excessive error conditions
    Sync Issues (Warning) - Block synchronization problems
    RPC Connection Errors (Warning) - API connectivity issues
    Peer Connection Issues (Warning) - Network connectivity problems
    Block Download Failures (Warning) - Blockchain download issues

Deployment Options
Local Development

# Quick start for testing and development
docker compose up -d

Production with Ansible

# Automated infrastructure deployment
./scripts/ansible-deploy.sh

Cloud Deployment

Supports deployment on:

    AWS EC2
    Google Cloud Platform
    Microsoft Azure
    Any Linux-based VPS

Verification

After deployment, verify the system is working correctly:

# Run comprehensive verification
./scripts/verify-deployment.sh

# Check individual services
docker compose ps
curl http://localhost:3000/api/health
curl http://localhost:3100/ready

